HEADWORD: Maara shell
<hw>Ma"a*ra shell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large,
pearly, spiral, marine shell (<spn>Turbo margaritaceus</spn>), from the
Pacific Islands. It is used as an ornament.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

